verbose_text: Concurrent elevated CRP and SCC-Ag serum levels correlated with the T status (P < 0.001), N stage (P < 0.001), lymph node metastasis with ECS (P = 0.003), tumor stage (P < 0.001), skin invasion (P < 0.001), bone invasion (P < 0.001), tumor depth> = 10 mm (P < 0.001), and perineural invasion (P = 0.056), whereas they did not correlate with the degree of tumor differentiation.
